snippet.textDisplay:
So for reference: A fetish in this context is synonymous with an effigy.
A fetish necklace, for example, is a necklace made up of one or more items carved or otherwise constructed to resemble a real life counterpart (usually an animal of some kind, but the Venus of Willendorf is also considered a fetish piece). The intent is that the fetish is imbued with some trait or power which the real version contains/owns (bear for strength, eagle for speed or grace, owl for wisdom, etc).
Its kind of like how "theory" in layman's terms means an idea or hypothesis, whereas a theory in academia is closer to what we would call a fact - same word, completely different meaning depending on the audience's background.
